Rather than taking precedent from personal feelings and opinions, the government could better gain support and enthusiasm for passing the longstanding abortion law by appealing to the Swiss women who remain faithfully in support of it. Additional deference should come from the voters within the cantons, who are given the opportunity to vote on popular initiatives. A task force has been proposed to investigate ways in which to promote the passing of a revised abortion law. According to the task-force chairman, no such unanimous consensus to re-write the new abortion bill exists. This is, consequently, a real challenge for the politicians (desautels).
